Use MAUI's `App` lifecycle events combined with `Preferences` for lightweight persistence:

**App.xaml.cs** — hook the lifecycle events:
```csharp
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);

    window.Deactivated += (s, e) =>
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppBackgroundMessage());

    window.Activated += (s, e) =>
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new AppForegroundMessage());

    return window;
}
```

**Messages:**
```csharp
public class AppBackgroundMessage { }
public class AppForegroundMessage { }
```

**NotesViewModel.cs** — save/restore the draft:
```csharp
public partial class NotesViewModel : ObservableObject, IRecipient<AppBackgroundMessage>, IRecipient<AppForegroundMessage>
{
    private const string DraftKey = "notes_draft";

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _draftText = string.Empty;

    public NotesViewModel()
    {
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.RegisterAll(this);
        RestoreDraft();              // also restore on first load
    }

    public void Receive(AppBackgroundMessage message) => SaveDraft();
    public void Receive(AppForegroundMessage message) => RestoreDraft();

    private void SaveDraft()
        => Preferences.Set(DraftKey, DraftText);

    private void RestoreDraft()
        => DraftText = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);

    // Call after a successful save-to-server to clear the draft
    public void ClearDraft()
    {
        DraftText = string.Empty;
        Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);
    }
}
```

**NotesPage.xaml** — bind the editor:
```xml
<Editor Text="{Binding DraftText}" Placeholder="Start typing..." />
```

**Key points:**

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| **When to save** | `Window.Deactivated` fires on background/lock |
| **Storage** | `Preferences` for small text; use `SecureStorage` or file I/O for large/sensitive content |
| **Decoupling** | `WeakReferenceMessenger` keeps `App` and VM independent |
| **Cleanup** | Call `ClearDraft()` after the user explicitly saves |

> `Preferences` has a platform-dependent size limit (~1 MB on Android). If notes can be large, write to a file in `FileSystem.AppDataDirectory` instead.
